article.description: — Dillon Jones had 26 points, 10 rebounds and six assists in Weber State's 83-78 victory against Oral Roberts on Saturday night.
article.headline: Jones scores 26 and grabs 10 rebounds as Weber State takes down Oral Roberts 83-78
article.linkText: Jones scores 26 and grabs 10 rebounds as Weber State takes down Oral Roberts 83-78
article.story: TULSA, Okla. -- — Dillon Jones had 26 points, 10 rebounds and six assists in Weber State's 83-78 victory against Oral Roberts on Saturday night. Dyson Koehler added 17 points for the Wildcats (11-4, 2-0). Blaise Threatt was 4-of-7 shooting and 5 of 6 from the free throw line to finish with 13 points. It was the sixth straight win for the Wildcats. The Golden Eagles (7-8) were led in scoring by Issac McBride, who finished with 29 points. Sir Issac Herron added 13 points and seven rebounds for Oral Roberts. Jailen Bedford also had 12 points and seven rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
